    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains 12 monthly observations of sales figures, forming a univariate time series with categorical temporal indexing. Synthetic data follows realistic retail patterns with \u03bc=$554.5k and \u03c3=$163.7k, showing summer peak (June: $843k) and holiday season decline (November: $312k). The column chart maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating gridlines while maintaining clear value comparisons through proportional column widths. Responsive formatting applies Cairo's preattentive processing principles by converting month labels to initials below 500px width, maintaining pattern recognition. Color choice (#5C7EAF) ensures accessibility with 4.5:1 contrast ratio against white background."
